org.thymeleaf.spring4.context
Class SpringWebContext

Object
  org.thymeleaf.context.AbstractContext
      org.thymeleaf.context.WebContext
          org.thymeleaf.spring4.context.SpringWebContext
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.thymeleaf.context.IContext, org.thymeleaf.context.IWebContext
public class SpringWebContext
extends org.thymeleaf.context.WebContext

Implementation of IContext meant for Spring MVC applications, extending WebContext and adding:

  • A special beans variable of class (Beans) that allows users to access beans in the application context. This variable can be accessed like any other variable in the context: ${beans.myBean.doSomething()}.
  • A reference to the Application Context itself, that can be obtained and used from element/attribute processors (getApplicationContext()).

Since:
1.0
Author:
Daniel Fernández, Josh Long
